@node "Bitmap_Obj_Introduction" "Introduction"

    Bitmap_Obj is an E object I have created to easyly manage 
    bitmaps, even True Colours ones.

    It  has  some good commands, and, as you can see, it may seems it miss some
others.  But it is not in this way:  Bitmap_obj comes with the "basic" commands
inside,  while  the  others  will  be  provided  as  "Add-Ons".  This is a good
mediation  between  OOP  and small code:  I could add a lot of controls to this
object,  but  the size would grow considerably:  so I have decided to implement
"Add-On",  and  I  think I have done the trick.  BTW:  I will share some source
code  about  how  to  create  "Add-Ons",  you  can  modify  it, creating faster
procedures, or just use it as a starting point to create NEW commands!  Please,
in both situation, send them to me with some documentation and the source code,
and I'll include them in next releases of this object.

    My goal with Bitmap_Obj is to create a flexible, easy to use and incredibly
powerful  object:   it  has  been designed for 24Bit graphic also, with an 8Bit
Alpha channel capability...  what do you want more ?? ;)

    Main features are:

        * Different OS2.0 and OS3.0 allocbitmap() method.

        * You can draw on this bitmap: it has a rastport.

        * 24Bit Support with 8Bit of Alpha channel capability.

        * Expandible via "Add-On"s.

@endnode

