@node "Bitmap_Obj_alloc" "Amiga-E Modules: Bitmap_Obj/allocbitmap()"
           NAME: allocbitmap(width, height, depth)

    DESCRIPTION: This command allocates a bitmap and a rastport for it.
                 It also frees all datas previously allocated on the same
                 object.

          INPUT: width                  - Bitmap width  (in pixels)
                 height                 - Bitmap height (in pixels)
                 depth                  - Bitmap depth  (1...8)

        RESULTS:

          RAISE: "MEM"        - If there is not enougth mem to allocate bitmap
                                or for the rastport.
                 "nlay"       - If it was unable to create the layer.
                 "blay"       - If it was unable to create behind layer.

       SEE ALSO: @{" freebitmap() " LINK Bitmap_obj_freebitmap}
@endnode

