@node "Bitmap_Obj_assign" "Amiga-E Modules: Bitmap_Obj/assign"
           NAME: assign(bitmap:PTR TO bitmap)

    DESCRIPTION: Use this command to "change" on the fly the bitmap
                 with a new one. Note that all datas of the previous
                 bitmap will be lost. And there will be no rastport
                 for this "stolen" bitmap.
                 Note also that the bitmap is not copied inside the
                 object, but the object keeps just a pointer to the
                 passed bitmap. So DO NOT FREE the bitmap before you
                 have closed the object (or re assign() ed it).

          INPUT: bitmap     - (PTR TO bitmap) a new bitmap to handle.

        RESULTS: NONE.

          RAISE:

       SEE ALSO:
@endnode

@node "Bitmap_Obj_truecol" "Amiga-E Modules: Bitmap_Obj/truecol"
           NAME: truecol()

    DESCRIPTION: This command allocates a true colour 32Bit picture with
                 the same size of the original 8Bit bitmap in memory.
                 NOTE: use this command only when you are SURE there is
                 a bitmap in memory. At the moment, it does not check
                 for valid values, so you have to do it for yourself.

          INPUT: NONE.

        RESULTS: NONE.

          RAISE: "MEM"  - If there is not enough memory.

       SEE ALSO: @{" freetruecol() " LINK Bitmap_obj_freetrue}
                 @{" gettruecol()  " LINK Bitmap_obj_gettrue}
@endnode

