@node Bitmap_obj_32Bit "32Bit Bitmap Specifications"

    My 32Bit bitmap is a chunky bitmap.
    When you call the truecol() method, I just alloc a chunk of memory
    of w*h*4 size.

    So here you can store your picture datas as chunky: a colour can have
    32Bit range, not just 24Bit per colour. This is very good because it
    offers a 24Bit colour picture and a 8Bit Alpha channel. 
    
    As you can see, inside my object there aren't 32Bit blitting or drawing
    primitives: they are inside bitmap_draw.m add-on. If you want to develop
    better add-ons, just have a look at the _complete_ code I have included
    about bitmap_draw.m module.

    If you obtain good results, why do not send it to me, so I can include
    it in the next release of these object? 
    My address is @{" here " LINK author}
@endnode
